Does National Liability and Fire Insurance Company Still Sell Insurance?














+32 votes














asked

Dec 31, 2012


by 
anonymous




Share on 

share on gp
share on fb
share on tw
share on li








 




 
 


 



Please log in or register to answer this question.
 


1 Answer










0 votes













National Liability and Fire Insurance Company is no longer selling insurance under that name. Instead the company was bought out by the Berkshire Hathaway Group, and its divisions either absorbed into other companies or transferred a Berkshire Hathaway company named National Indemnity Insurance.
Financial RatingNational Liability and Fire Insurance Company is an unusual case, as the company was eventually absorbed into the parent company which had owned it from the beginning. Because of that, the parent company rating was always applied to National Liability and Fire Insurance Company. That rating, at the very top of financial ratings in the industry, is "A++ (Superior), with a long term financial outlook of "aaa (stable)."
Products the Company SoldNational Liability and Fire Insurance Company, as the name implied was a specialty and commercial insurance company. National Liability and Fire Insurance Company was a commercial insurer specializing in commercial vehicles, business insurance and such specialty coverage as garage insurance. Even though the National Liability and Fire Insurance Company is no longer in existence, the policies it carried are still available through National Indemnity Company and underwritten by the same company that has backed those polices for decades: Berkshire Hathaway the owner of GEICO.
What Happened to the Company?Since being absorbed by the Berkshire Hathaway group, little of the history of National Liability and Fire Insurance Company is known today. However, this absorption was not a sudden event, as happens to many insurance companies. Instead, the acquisition took place more than 40 years ago, when a subsidiary of Berkshire, the National Indemnity Company, acquired a company known as the Home and Automobile Insurance Company in 1971. This company was later renamed National Liability and Fire Insurance Company, and eventually became absorbed into the parent company.




answered

Dec 31, 2012


by 
anonymous









 




